            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://losangeles.craigslist.org/lgb/fbh/6046671413.html"></div>
        </div>
<b><i>Parkers' Lighthouse</i></b> is looking for an <b>Assistant Service Manager</b>.  The ideal candidate will be a seasoned restaurant professional with a service-oriented approach and a genuine interest in hospitality and ensuring that each guest has an exceptional experience.<br><br>

<b><i>Specific Requirements</b></i><br>
- A MINIMUM OF 2 YEARS OF EXPERIENCE with FOH management in a high-volume, fine dining environment<br>
- a commitment to providing exceptional service to every guest<br>
- the ability to work well with people<br>
- a thorough knowledge of restaurant operations<br>
<br>
<i><b>Compensation</b></i><br>
Commensurate with experience.  Medical and dental benefits, 401(k) available. <br>
<br>
<i><b>For Consideration</b></i><br>

Please e-mail resume to the address above, using "ASM - Long Beach - [Your Name]" as the subject line. Please do not apply in person.<br>
<br>
<i><b>Overview</b></i><br>
The Assistant Service Manager is an executive exempt position responsible for assisting in the operation of the service department. Primary duties include directing the work of other employees within the department. Particular weight is given to the hiring, firing, and promoting of other employees. <br>
<br>
<i><b>Specific Responsibilities</b></i><br>

1. Assisting in directing the work of the employees within the department, which includes suggesting and recommending the hiring, firing and promotion of other employees and assisting in inducting employees to properly staff the service department.<br>


2. Ensuring positive guest relations, which includes making all guests feel welcome by cordially greeting them, making them feel important, always speaking in positives and thanking each guest as they leave the restaurant.<br>


3. Adhering to the proper steps of service. <br>


4. Completing weekly employee schedules based on budgeted labor cost.<br>

5. Maintaining the Company's employee training standards, which includes using training manuals, daily training programs and knowledge checks and assisting in conducting daily sales meetings with employees.<br>

6. Maintaining safety and security procedures.<br>


7. Maintaining positive employee relations, which includes assisting with assessing, counseling and reviewing job performance of service employees to maintain a total employee turnover rate below 50%.    </section>

